# Core Principles

## Scope
This rule applies universally to all AI-assisted code generation in this project.

## Purpose
AI Coding Assistants should accelerate development, improve documentation and tests, and reduce repetitive work while avoiding subtle bugs, increased review load, or architectural drift.

## Core Principles

- Use disciplined workflows with clear constraints
- Maintain strong review practices
- Work in small, reviewable increments
- Prioritize correctness and simplicity over cleverness
- Always consider edge cases and risks
- Prefer static typing and type-checker feedback over intuition
- Use stateless terminal commands (each command should be runnable independently)
- Verify API details against authoritative docs when uncertain
- Keep files under 64KB for reliable operation

## Rationale
These principles ensure AI assistance enhances productivity without compromising code quality or introducing technical debt.

